WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:19.186 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.186 --> 00:00:20.621 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
Perhaps highest

00:00:20.621 --> 00:00:23.156 align:middle line:10%
on our list of stressors,
aside from a life-threatening

00:00:23.156 --> 00:00:25.626 align:middle line:10%
illness, is our
personal finances.

00:00:25.626 --> 00:00:28.662 align:middle line:10%
For this reason, I'm looking
at money from all directions.

00:00:28.662 --> 00:00:31.598 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, others are out
there creating solutions.

00:00:31.598 --> 00:00:33.800 align:middle line:10%
Today, we're speaking with
Michael Tellinger, who

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:36.737 align:middle line:10%
has a big plan for the people
of his native country, South

00:00:36.737 --> 00:00:37.771 align:middle line:10%
Africa.

00:00:37.771 --> 00:00:41.475 align:middle line:84%
Unemployment there is
hovering around 40% to 50%

00:00:41.475 --> 00:00:44.344 align:middle line:84%
with little hope of a
return to good times.

00:00:44.344 --> 00:00:47.214 align:middle line:84%
Michael's plan would bring
prosperity and dignity back

00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:49.483 align:middle line:90%
to life in his homeland.

00:00:49.483 --> 00:00:51.752 align:middle line:90%
It's called Ubuntu.

00:00:51.752 --> 00:00:53.854 align:middle line:84%
And Michael, thank you
for joining us today.

00:00:53.854 --> 00:00:56.056 align:middle line:84%
This is a subject near and
dear to my heart as well.

00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:57.291 align:middle line:90%
>>MICHAEL TELLINGER: Oh yeah.

00:00:57.291 --> 00:00:58.225 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The
stresses, and you've

00:00:58.225 --> 00:00:59.893 align:middle line:84%
been putting a lot
of thought into this.

00:00:59.893 --> 00:01:02.396 align:middle line:84%
But first of all,
I'd like for you

00:01:02.396 --> 00:01:04.864 align:middle line:84%
to make the link between
your previous discoveries

00:01:04.864 --> 00:01:06.700 align:middle line:84%
in the books you've
written, which

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:11.405 align:middle line:84%
were about the inhabitation
of the South African lands

00:01:11.405 --> 00:01:14.641 align:middle line:84%
by species from another planet
that created a worker bee

00:01:14.641 --> 00:01:17.244 align:middle line:84%
species that became what
we know as the human being

00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:19.146 align:middle line:90%
for the purposes of mining gold.

00:01:19.146 --> 00:01:20.948 align:middle line:84%
Now, we talked about
that at great length

00:01:20.948 --> 00:01:22.316 align:middle line:90%
in another interview.

00:01:22.316 --> 00:01:25.519 align:middle line:84%
But how did that lead you
into the notion of Ubuntu?

00:01:25.519 --> 00:01:27.420 align:middle line:84%
And you're really putting
yourself on the line

00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:29.957 align:middle line:84%
because you're starting a new
political party in South Africa

00:01:29.957 --> 00:01:31.191 align:middle line:90%
by the same name.

00:01:31.191 --> 00:01:32.125 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yeah.

00:01:32.125 --> 00:01:34.494 align:middle line:10%
These things all
happen in a sequence

00:01:34.494 --> 00:01:37.364 align:middle line:10%
of events that sometimes
take you by surprise.

00:01:37.364 --> 00:01:39.098 align:middle line:10%
And I was taken
by surprise when I

00:01:39.098 --> 00:01:42.569 align:middle line:10%
started researching the
origins of humankind.

00:01:42.569 --> 00:01:43.070 align:middle line:90%
Who are we?

00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:44.037 align:middle line:90%
Where do we come from?

00:01:44.037 --> 00:01:45.472 align:middle line:90%
Why are we here as a species?

00:01:45.472 --> 00:01:47.207 align:middle line:84%
And reaching
startling conclusions

00:01:47.207 --> 00:01:50.676 align:middle line:84%
that suddenly are now becoming
more and more mainstream

00:01:50.676 --> 00:01:53.580 align:middle line:84%
theories and providing
the physical evidence

00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:56.450 align:middle line:84%
and scientific evidence for
who we are as a species.

00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:58.085 align:middle line:10%
But what struck me
is when you start

00:01:58.085 --> 00:02:02.055 align:middle line:10%
looking at the translations
of the Sumerian tablets

00:02:02.055 --> 00:02:05.025 align:middle line:10%
and the work that
Zecharia Sitchin has done

00:02:05.025 --> 00:02:07.995 align:middle line:10%
and pretty much all
other translations

00:02:07.995 --> 00:02:14.034 align:middle line:10%
that are available, the concept
and the subject of money

00:02:14.034 --> 00:02:18.839 align:middle line:10%
does not arise among
the so-called gods.

00:02:18.839 --> 00:02:22.909 align:middle line:84%
It only seems to appear
when humans enter the scene.

00:02:22.909 --> 00:02:26.913 align:middle line:84%
And it only seems to appear
when the control and the abuse

00:02:26.913 --> 00:02:30.751 align:middle line:84%
of humanity is at
stake or at question.

00:02:30.751 --> 00:02:35.522 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that for
probably the first 280,000

00:02:35.522 --> 00:02:39.893 align:middle line:84%
years of our existence as a
species, we did not have money.

00:02:39.893 --> 00:02:42.129 align:middle line:84%
We might have been a
lower consciousness level

00:02:42.129 --> 00:02:47.167 align:middle line:84%
species as we were evolving into
the state that we're in now,

00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:51.004 align:middle line:84%
growing and exploding
in consciousness.

00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:54.074 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
we didn't have money.

00:02:54.074 --> 00:02:57.110 align:middle line:84%
And we survived for much
longer periods of time

00:02:57.110 --> 00:03:00.647 align:middle line:84%
without the concept
of money than we

00:03:00.647 --> 00:03:04.317 align:middle line:84%
have had the use of money
in our known history

00:03:04.317 --> 00:03:06.420 align:middle line:90%
or our imagined history.

00:03:06.420 --> 00:03:11.425 align:middle line:84%
So the question begs, how
and why was money introduced?

00:03:11.425 --> 00:03:16.063 align:middle line:84%
How and why is money
used by the human race?

00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:18.965 align:middle line:84%
And the answers to that
are far more strange

00:03:18.965 --> 00:03:20.700 align:middle line:90%
than most people realize.

00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:21.401 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Indeed.

00:03:21.401 --> 00:03:24.237 align:middle line:84%
And not only that, I mean, there
are certain theories out there

00:03:24.237 --> 00:03:25.972 align:middle line:84%
and certain people's
works, in fact,

00:03:25.972 --> 00:03:30.177 align:middle line:84%
that would even refer to
money almost as a virus that

00:03:30.177 --> 00:03:33.880 align:middle line:84%
has been injected into
our communal way of life,

00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:36.616 align:middle line:90%
our psyche, into our cultures.

00:03:36.616 --> 00:03:38.051 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: It's
very clear to me

00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:42.722 align:middle line:84%
now that the big separation,
the dividing line

00:03:42.722 --> 00:03:46.493 align:middle line:84%
in pre-human history and the
sort of history that we would

00:03:46.493 --> 00:03:50.831 align:middle line:84%
refer to today is the great
flood, the biblical flood.

00:03:50.831 --> 00:03:53.934 align:middle line:84%
That seems to be a really
important dividing line

00:03:53.934 --> 00:03:55.368 align:middle line:90%
in all of human history.

00:03:55.368 --> 00:03:58.438 align:middle line:84%
And it's only after
the flood, which

00:03:58.438 --> 00:04:01.708 align:middle line:84%
happened between 12,000
and 13,000 years ago,--

00:04:01.708 --> 00:04:03.944 align:middle line:84%
And that seems to
be an historic event

00:04:03.944 --> 00:04:07.280 align:middle line:84%
that most geologists and
historians and archaeologists

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:11.485 align:middle line:84%
tend to agree upon with
very little squabbling.

00:04:11.485 --> 00:04:14.221 align:middle line:84%
It's only after the flood
that this magical thing

00:04:14.221 --> 00:04:17.724 align:middle line:84%
called money suddenly
pops its head up.

00:04:17.724 --> 00:04:24.798 align:middle line:10%
And it seems to coincide with
what Sumerian tablets refer

00:04:24.798 --> 00:04:31.104 align:middle line:10%
to as, and it's a recurring
Sumerian tablet translation, is

00:04:31.104 --> 00:04:34.541 align:middle line:10%
when kingdom was lowered
to earth from heaven.

00:04:34.541 --> 00:04:38.545 align:middle line:84%
And you find these translations
in several Sumerian tablets,

00:04:38.545 --> 00:04:44.718 align:middle line:84%
when the gods appointed kings
on earth and high priests

00:04:44.718 --> 00:04:46.853 align:middle line:90%
to rule over the people.

00:04:46.853 --> 00:04:50.090 align:middle line:84%
Part of that appointment,
after the flood,

00:04:50.090 --> 00:04:52.292 align:middle line:84%
was the introduction
of this thing called

00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:55.629 align:middle line:84%
money that was then
used to control

00:04:55.629 --> 00:04:59.032 align:middle line:84%
the humanity by the royal
bloodlines, which incidentally

00:04:59.032 --> 00:05:00.433 align:middle line:90%
we still have today.

00:05:00.433 --> 00:05:01.968 align:middle line:90%
Nothing has changed.

00:05:01.968 --> 00:05:04.471 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That is true,
and the manipulation

00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:07.340 align:middle line:84%
of the human species through
the monetary systems.

00:05:07.340 --> 00:05:09.843 align:middle line:84%
And recently, I told you
off camera about this,

00:05:09.843 --> 00:05:11.845 align:middle line:84%
I interviewed a man named
Stephen Belgin as well

00:05:11.845 --> 00:05:13.280 align:middle line:90%
on the subject of money.

00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:16.516 align:middle line:84%
And what he was
talking about was

00:05:16.516 --> 00:05:22.389 align:middle line:84%
how the local localities,
local companies, a coal mining

00:05:22.389 --> 00:05:27.294 align:middle line:84%
company in one case, small towns
at various points in history,

00:05:27.294 --> 00:05:30.997 align:middle line:84%
dating back about 1,000 years
ago and forward to this time,

00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:34.968 align:middle line:84%
were creative enough to be able,
in hard times, when currencies

00:05:34.968 --> 00:05:38.071 align:middle line:84%
had gone down and people
had fallen into deprivation

00:05:38.071 --> 00:05:41.975 align:middle line:84%
and even depression, they
were able to organize and find

00:05:41.975 --> 00:05:46.379 align:middle line:84%
ways of pulling together and
very rapidly brang-- brought

00:05:46.379 --> 00:05:49.182 align:middle line:84%
their community back up into
a high state of function

00:05:49.182 --> 00:05:50.784 align:middle line:90%
again with prosperity.

00:05:50.784 --> 00:05:52.219 align:middle line:84%
And then, the
reason I bring it up

00:05:52.219 --> 00:05:53.587 align:middle line:84%
is because of what
you just said.

00:05:53.587 --> 00:05:57.224 align:middle line:84%
And then it would be
the king, who would--

00:05:57.224 --> 00:05:58.692 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: Stamp
his authority.

00:05:58.692 --> 00:06:00.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --stamp his
authority and say, hey,

00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:02.729 align:middle line:84%
the monetary system
that exists currently,

00:06:02.729 --> 00:06:04.097 align:middle line:84%
we're feeling
threatened by this.

00:06:04.097 --> 00:06:05.899 align:middle line:84%
And then they would
outlaw the use

00:06:05.899 --> 00:06:07.934 align:middle line:84%
of whatever the
other complimentary

00:06:07.934 --> 00:06:09.669 align:middle line:90%
form of trade or currency was.

00:06:09.669 --> 00:06:11.271 align:middle line:84%
And this has
happened repeatedly.

00:06:11.271 --> 00:06:12.038 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yeah.

00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:15.875 align:middle line:84%
You know, the money thing is
a really fascinating subject

00:06:15.875 --> 00:06:21.748 align:middle line:84%
to talk about because we are so
lost and consumed with money.

00:06:21.748 --> 00:06:24.451 align:middle line:84%
We can't imagine a
world without money.

00:06:24.451 --> 00:06:26.987 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I
find so fascinating.

00:06:26.987 --> 00:06:29.889 align:middle line:84%
Is if you allow
yourself the freedom

00:06:29.889 --> 00:06:32.859 align:middle line:84%
to imagine a world without money
and how it will dramatically

00:06:32.859 --> 00:06:36.296 align:middle line:84%
change everything we do,
the way we think, the way we

00:06:36.296 --> 00:06:38.798 align:middle line:84%
behave towards each
other, the way we act,

00:06:38.798 --> 00:06:41.835 align:middle line:84%
what we choose to do in our
lives, how we build things,

00:06:41.835 --> 00:06:44.437 align:middle line:84%
how we live, how we
educate, how we heal,

00:06:44.437 --> 00:06:48.875 align:middle line:84%
how we use energy--
it affects everything

00:06:48.875 --> 00:06:51.177 align:middle line:90%
dramatically and profoundly.

00:06:51.177 --> 00:06:53.647 align:middle line:84%
It takes the entire
social structure

00:06:53.647 --> 00:06:57.984 align:middle line:84%
as we have as a species
and turns it on its head.

00:06:57.984 --> 00:07:01.254 align:middle line:84%
And at this point, I
need to, as I normally

00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:05.492 align:middle line:84%
do in my presentations, say how
did we get into this situation?

00:07:05.492 --> 00:07:09.863 align:middle line:84%
How did we get into this
mess that we face today?

00:07:09.863 --> 00:07:14.701 align:middle line:84%
Global economic collapse
is looming, is imminent.

00:07:14.701 --> 00:07:20.473 align:middle line:84%
Most, sort of,
levelheaded economists

00:07:20.473 --> 00:07:23.276 align:middle line:84%
are startled at the
fact that there is still

00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:26.112 align:middle line:84%
a global economy, that it hasn't
just collapsed or imploded

00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:26.746 align:middle line:90%
in some way.

00:07:26.746 --> 00:07:27.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:07:27.380 --> 00:07:29.049 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: How is
it still continuing?

00:07:29.049 --> 00:07:32.485 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think the answer to
that is relatively simple.

00:07:32.485 --> 00:07:36.089 align:middle line:84%
It's because the power that the
banking families and the royal

00:07:36.089 --> 00:07:39.259 align:middle line:84%
bloodlines that go back
thousands of years.

00:07:39.259 --> 00:07:40.727 align:middle line:84%
This is not something
that happened

00:07:40.727 --> 00:07:42.595 align:middle line:90%
100 years ago or 200 years ago.

00:07:42.595 --> 00:07:44.597 align:middle line:84%
This goes back
thousands of years

00:07:44.597 --> 00:07:47.400 align:middle line:84%
of control and manipulation
of the human race.

00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:50.770 align:middle line:84%
And money, at one point,
became the key tool

00:07:50.770 --> 00:07:53.606 align:middle line:90%
of control, absolute control.

00:07:53.606 --> 00:07:56.476 align:middle line:84%
And they're so powerful
that they can really

00:07:56.476 --> 00:08:00.380 align:middle line:84%
keep it propped up for
as long as they possibly

00:08:00.380 --> 00:08:05.185 align:middle line:84%
can until we, the people,
decide that's enough.

00:08:05.185 --> 00:08:07.187 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet,
at the same time,

00:08:07.187 --> 00:08:09.789 align:middle line:84%
they keep it propped
up, yet scarce.

00:08:09.789 --> 00:08:10.824 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Very scarce.

00:08:10.824 --> 00:08:13.626 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Scarcity seems to
be really at the basis of this

00:08:13.626 --> 00:08:18.765 align:middle line:84%
because if you can't create a
fear of some kind surrounding

00:08:18.765 --> 00:08:21.935 align:middle line:84%
any given subject, especially
money, which relates

00:08:21.935 --> 00:08:24.037 align:middle line:84%
to our survival, our
sense of survival.

00:08:24.037 --> 00:08:27.907 align:middle line:84%
If you can't create fear--
Scarcity equals fear.

00:08:27.907 --> 00:08:30.677 align:middle line:84%
If you can't create fear,
you can't control people.

00:08:30.677 --> 00:08:33.413 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: Well, that's
what you opened up by saying,

00:08:33.413 --> 00:08:36.049 align:middle line:84%
one of the biggest stressors
we have is financial stress.

00:08:36.049 --> 00:08:38.118 align:middle line:84%
Well, why do we have
financial stress?

00:08:38.118 --> 00:08:39.885 align:middle line:90%
Why do we allow ourselves?

00:08:39.885 --> 00:08:41.821 align:middle line:90%
How do we get to this point?

00:08:41.821 --> 00:08:43.222 align:middle line:90%
And that's the beautiful story.

00:08:43.222 --> 00:08:46.126 align:middle line:84%
When the lights go on and
you realize what's going on,

00:08:46.126 --> 00:08:50.330 align:middle line:84%
you go, how could I have
been so stupid to buy

00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:52.065 align:middle line:90%
into that kind of system?

00:08:52.065 --> 00:08:54.768 align:middle line:84%
Because it's an absolute
control and manipulation

00:08:54.768 --> 00:08:58.505 align:middle line:84%
system, where a small number
of humans, individuals,

00:08:58.505 --> 00:09:01.307 align:middle line:84%
have taken on the
right to print money

00:09:01.307 --> 00:09:04.444 align:middle line:84%
and to create money out of
thin air, out of nothing

00:09:04.444 --> 00:09:07.247 align:middle line:84%
and make us, the
rest of humanity,

00:09:07.247 --> 00:09:09.516 align:middle line:90%
use that thing that they create.

00:09:09.516 --> 00:09:12.085 align:middle line:84%
And if we don't have it,
oh, you're in big trouble.

00:09:12.085 --> 00:09:13.219 align:middle line:90%
You're in big, big trouble.

00:09:13.219 --> 00:09:14.254 align:middle line:90%
You don't have any money?

00:09:14.254 --> 00:09:15.054 align:middle line:90%
Oh my goodness.

00:09:15.054 --> 00:09:16.656 align:middle line:84%
Now, you're going
to become a vagrant.

00:09:16.656 --> 00:09:18.391 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to
become a criminal.

00:09:18.391 --> 00:09:21.494 align:middle line:84%
From the moment we breathe
our first breath when

00:09:21.494 --> 00:09:24.264 align:middle line:84%
we are born to the moment
we breathe our last breath,

00:09:24.264 --> 00:09:25.865 align:middle line:90%
it's all about money.

00:09:25.865 --> 00:09:30.136 align:middle line:84%
And people that deny that
are just fooling themselves

00:09:30.136 --> 00:09:32.305 align:middle line:84%
until they wake
up and realize it.

00:09:32.305 --> 00:09:33.673 align:middle line:90%
We can do something about it.

00:09:33.673 --> 00:09:36.075 align:middle line:84%
It's up to us to do
something about that.

00:09:36.075 --> 00:09:37.577 align:middle line:90%
And I think the time has come.

00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:38.578 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It has come.

00:09:38.578 --> 00:09:40.046 align:middle line:84%
Now, you're doing
something that's

00:09:40.046 --> 00:09:42.048 align:middle line:84%
really fascinating, which
we're going to get to.

00:09:42.048 --> 00:09:45.118 align:middle line:84%
Other people have actually
tried creating new currencies

00:09:45.118 --> 00:09:46.786 align:middle line:90%
and introducing new currencies.

00:09:46.786 --> 00:09:48.521 align:middle line:84%
Some of them have
ended up in jail,

00:09:48.521 --> 00:09:49.956 align:middle line:90%
as a result of their efforts.

00:09:49.956 --> 00:09:52.492 align:middle line:84%
You are not allowed to
create a new currency.

00:09:52.492 --> 00:09:54.327 align:middle line:84%
There are very
specific protocols.

00:09:54.327 --> 00:09:57.464 align:middle line:84%
Certain communities in the
United States, for example,

00:09:57.464 --> 00:10:01.534 align:middle line:84%
have successfully created
an alternative currency.

00:10:01.534 --> 00:10:04.771 align:middle line:84%
But still, you're getting
into very problematic areas.

00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:08.808 align:middle line:84%
But what you're talking
about does not necessarily

00:10:08.808 --> 00:10:10.477 align:middle line:90%
involve currencies.

00:10:10.477 --> 00:10:11.344 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: No.

00:10:11.344 --> 00:10:14.581 align:middle line:84%
I'm suggesting something
completely the opposite.

00:10:14.581 --> 00:10:17.350 align:middle line:84%
If money is the
tool of all problems

00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:20.186 align:middle line:84%
and the tool of
absolute control, which

00:10:20.186 --> 00:10:23.389 align:middle line:84%
we can show very quickly
that that's what it is,

00:10:23.389 --> 00:10:28.862 align:middle line:84%
then how do we escape
that absolute control?

00:10:28.862 --> 00:10:31.264 align:middle line:84%
By removing money
from the system.

00:10:31.264 --> 00:10:34.267 align:middle line:84%
And when you say that to people,
most people jump up and down

00:10:34.267 --> 00:10:35.602 align:middle line:90%
and go, how is it going to work?

00:10:35.602 --> 00:10:37.103 align:middle line:84%
How are we going
to pay for things?

00:10:37.103 --> 00:10:39.105 align:middle line:84%
Why should I do this or
why should I do that?

00:10:39.105 --> 00:10:41.074 align:middle line:84%
If there's no money,
what incentive is there?

00:10:41.074 --> 00:10:42.542 align:middle line:90%
You know, people are lazy.

00:10:42.542 --> 00:10:43.910 align:middle line:84%
They're not going
to do anything.

00:10:43.910 --> 00:10:46.379 align:middle line:84%
All those arguments
and notions are

00:10:46.379 --> 00:10:50.650 align:middle line:84%
based on the capitalistic
and consumeristic principles

00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:53.086 align:middle line:90%
that we have been brought up on.

00:10:53.086 --> 00:10:55.522 align:middle line:84%
We cannot imagine a world
without money where people

00:10:55.522 --> 00:10:59.626 align:middle line:84%
actually live out their lives
using the God-given talents

00:10:59.626 --> 00:11:02.529 align:middle line:84%
or they acquired
skills that they--

00:11:02.529 --> 00:11:05.098 align:middle line:84%
passions that they pursued
because of what it is they love

00:11:05.098 --> 00:11:09.435 align:middle line:84%
to do, and using that as their
contribution to their society.

00:11:09.435 --> 00:11:11.771 align:middle line:84%
And that brings us
to the key word here.

00:11:11.771 --> 00:11:16.142 align:middle line:84%
In Africa, it is an age old
tradition known as Ubuntu.

00:11:16.142 --> 00:11:20.013 align:middle line:10%
And I call it contributionism,
which is something

00:11:20.013 --> 00:11:22.181 align:middle line:10%
that I deduced out
of writing my book,

00:11:22.181 --> 00:11:24.984 align:middle line:10%
"Slave Species of God,"
realizing that money was

00:11:24.984 --> 00:11:26.920 align:middle line:10%
maliciously introduced
to the human race

00:11:26.920 --> 00:11:30.123 align:middle line:10%
as a tool of control,
and the way we overcome

00:11:30.123 --> 00:11:33.626 align:middle line:10%
that is the way that people
lived for hundreds of thousands

00:11:33.626 --> 00:11:36.429 align:middle line:10%
of years, without money.

00:11:36.429 --> 00:11:37.964 align:middle line:84%
How do people live
without money?

00:11:37.964 --> 00:11:40.099 align:middle line:84%
By contributing
towards the greater

00:11:40.099 --> 00:11:41.200 align:middle line:90%
good of their communities.

00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:43.603 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk about
the African version of that.

00:11:43.603 --> 00:11:44.871 align:middle line:90%
What is the spirit of Ubuntu?

00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:47.574 align:middle line:84%
And how has that been
employed in Africa?

00:11:47.574 --> 00:11:49.475 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: Well, it's
an age old tradition,

00:11:49.475 --> 00:11:52.045 align:middle line:84%
not just in Africa, but
at all native populations

00:11:52.045 --> 00:11:53.379 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:58.718 align:middle line:84%
They all seem to have
the same human motive.

00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:02.922 align:middle line:84%
And that is if it's not good for
everyone, it's no good at all.

00:12:02.922 --> 00:12:07.226 align:middle line:84%
And that's a beautiful,
simplistic point of view.

00:12:07.226 --> 00:12:10.263 align:middle line:10%
What I need to remind
your viewers of

00:12:10.263 --> 00:12:13.900 align:middle line:10%
is that when the colonialists
arrived in Africa,

00:12:13.900 --> 00:12:15.668 align:middle line:10%
there was no homelessness.

00:12:15.668 --> 00:12:17.337 align:middle line:90%
There was no hunger.

00:12:17.337 --> 00:12:19.505 align:middle line:90%
There was no unemployment.

00:12:19.505 --> 00:12:22.709 align:middle line:84%
There were tribes living
in absolute abundance.

00:12:22.709 --> 00:12:25.845 align:middle line:84%
And if the tribe went hungry,
then everybody went hungry.

00:12:25.845 --> 00:12:30.516 align:middle line:84%
You didn't have homeless people
within the tribes wandering

00:12:30.516 --> 00:12:31.184 align:middle line:90%
around.

00:12:31.184 --> 00:12:33.486 align:middle line:90%
It was a controlled system.

00:12:33.486 --> 00:12:35.722 align:middle line:84%
And Ubuntu is at the
foundation of this.

00:12:35.722 --> 00:12:37.590 align:middle line:84%
It's an ancient
African tradition.

00:12:37.590 --> 00:12:40.994 align:middle line:84%
But all native populations
have those same traditions.

00:12:40.994 --> 00:12:45.965 align:middle line:84%
It is the colonization that
started some 500 years ago

00:12:45.965 --> 00:12:48.334 align:middle line:84%
that, as we discussed in
the previous interview,

00:12:48.334 --> 00:12:51.404 align:middle line:90%
severed us from our ancestors.

00:12:51.404 --> 00:12:55.174 align:middle line:84%
And the atrocities that
the colonizers perpetrated

00:12:55.174 --> 00:12:57.677 align:middle line:84%
in all the different
parts of the world, that

00:12:57.677 --> 00:13:01.014 align:middle line:84%
severed the native people
from their ancestors,

00:13:01.014 --> 00:13:03.683 align:middle line:84%
brought in so-called
civilization

00:13:03.683 --> 00:13:06.919 align:middle line:84%
and bring in modernization
and technology.

00:13:06.919 --> 00:13:08.688 align:middle line:90%
They introduced money.

00:13:08.688 --> 00:13:13.326 align:middle line:84%
They introduced ownership
of land and things

00:13:13.326 --> 00:13:15.895 align:middle line:84%
that were really quite alien
because the ancient cultures

00:13:15.895 --> 00:13:18.798 align:middle line:84%
believed that the land
belonged to the divine.

00:13:18.798 --> 00:13:20.800 align:middle line:84%
We were just
inhabiting the land,

00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:23.336 align:middle line:84%
and you've got to use
the land with respect.

00:13:23.336 --> 00:13:25.405 align:middle line:84%
So these are some of the
fundamental principles

00:13:25.405 --> 00:13:28.941 align:middle line:84%
that I'm bringing back
through the philosophies

00:13:28.941 --> 00:13:31.544 align:middle line:84%
that I've been putting
together since 2005,

00:13:31.544 --> 00:13:33.846 align:middle line:84%
called contributionism
or Ubuntu.

00:13:33.846 --> 00:13:37.050 align:middle line:10%
And I really call it
Ubuntu contributionism

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:41.587 align:middle line:10%
because it's a subtle twist on
the original Ubuntu principles

00:13:41.587 --> 00:13:43.956 align:middle line:10%
because we need to
keep moving forward

00:13:43.956 --> 00:13:47.093 align:middle line:10%
by utilizing the
best of the past.

00:13:47.093 --> 00:13:49.262 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Before we get
into the mechanics of that--

00:13:49.262 --> 00:13:51.998 align:middle line:84%
And we have a huge discussion
ahead about education

00:13:51.998 --> 00:13:54.834 align:middle line:84%
because we really have to
start over as a species,

00:13:54.834 --> 00:13:59.505 align:middle line:84%
in terms of raising each
other, raising our children.

00:13:59.505 --> 00:14:02.575 align:middle line:84%
Where we are, as a result
of the Industrial Revolution

00:14:02.575 --> 00:14:05.645 align:middle line:84%
and technology, I'm sure that
there are many people listening

00:14:05.645 --> 00:14:08.748 align:middle line:84%
to this right now
thinking, but I

00:14:08.748 --> 00:14:10.750 align:middle line:84%
don't want to just
live close to the land.

00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:12.785 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to be
without my stuff

00:14:12.785 --> 00:14:15.855 align:middle line:84%
because we've learned to
acquire and desire stuff.

00:14:15.855 --> 00:14:17.623 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: We consume,
consume, consume.

00:14:17.623 --> 00:14:19.826 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We cannot remember
what it was like to live

00:14:19.826 --> 00:14:21.894 align:middle line:84%
simply, where you have
shorter work days,

00:14:21.894 --> 00:14:23.896 align:middle line:84%
where you're with your
family, where you're with

00:14:23.896 --> 00:14:27.333 align:middle line:84%
your children, where
you help each other out.

00:14:27.333 --> 00:14:29.969 align:middle line:84%
Now, how does that part factor
in when you discuss this?

00:14:29.969 --> 00:14:31.537 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this has to
be a consideration

00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:32.338 align:middle line:90%
of a lot of people.

00:14:32.338 --> 00:14:34.407 align:middle line:90%
But I want my iPhone.

00:14:34.407 --> 00:14:36.075 align:middle line:90%
And so how does that--

00:14:36.075 --> 00:14:38.611 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: I think these are
very important considerations.

00:14:38.611 --> 00:14:42.815 align:middle line:84%
And we've compiled a set
of questions that I ask.

00:14:42.815 --> 00:14:45.451 align:middle line:84%
I've been through this thousands
and thousands of times.

00:14:45.451 --> 00:14:47.653 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, maybe we
can get to those at the end.

00:14:47.653 --> 00:14:49.489 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: But I
think, just to put people

00:14:49.489 --> 00:14:53.059 align:middle line:84%
at ease, whatever you're
thinking right now, I virtually

00:14:53.059 --> 00:14:55.595 align:middle line:84%
can guarantee you I've
been asked those questions

00:14:55.595 --> 00:14:56.963 align:middle line:90%
thousands of times.

00:14:56.963 --> 00:14:59.799 align:middle line:84%
The answers to every possible
hurdle you might have come up

00:14:59.799 --> 00:15:03.870 align:middle line:84%
with in our capitalistic,
consumeristic perspective

00:15:03.870 --> 00:15:06.672 align:middle line:84%
is like, what's in it
for me, me, me, me.

00:15:06.672 --> 00:15:08.508 align:middle line:84%
I've answered most
of those questions.

00:15:08.508 --> 00:15:10.910 align:middle line:84%
What I've had to do is
look at society today.

00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:12.044 align:middle line:90%
What is it that we do?

00:15:12.044 --> 00:15:13.379 align:middle line:90%
How do we function?

00:15:13.379 --> 00:15:15.715 align:middle line:84%
And I've looked at all the
different areas of society,

00:15:15.715 --> 00:15:18.451 align:middle line:84%
whether it's education,
whether it's arts and culture,

00:15:18.451 --> 00:15:24.056 align:middle line:84%
whether it's science and
technology, whether it's food,

00:15:24.056 --> 00:15:27.527 align:middle line:84%
providing of food and
community, all those areas I've

00:15:27.527 --> 00:15:29.996 align:middle line:84%
had to look at and
figure out solutions.

00:15:29.996 --> 00:15:33.800 align:middle line:84%
How is this going to work
in a moneyless society?

00:15:33.800 --> 00:15:35.935 align:middle line:84%
Which it worked for
long periods of time.

00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:38.070 align:middle line:84%
But now, if we had to remove
money from the system,

00:15:38.070 --> 00:15:39.605 align:middle line:90%
how is it going to work?

00:15:39.605 --> 00:15:44.343 align:middle line:84%
And the answers are so
simple, so incredibly simple,

00:15:44.343 --> 00:15:48.414 align:middle line:84%
that when it hits you
is the most exciting,

00:15:48.414 --> 00:15:51.484 align:middle line:84%
mind-blowing moment
in your life,

00:15:51.484 --> 00:15:53.920 align:middle line:84%
that you'll remember that
moment forever and ever.

00:15:53.920 --> 00:15:56.189 align:middle line:84%
It's like this
huge concrete block

00:15:56.189 --> 00:15:58.191 align:middle line:84%
that's being lifted
off your chest when

00:15:58.191 --> 00:16:00.226 align:middle line:84%
you realize how
simple it all is.

00:16:00.226 --> 00:16:01.327 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, what a tease.

00:16:01.327 --> 00:16:04.096 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: And how
poisoned our minds

00:16:04.096 --> 00:16:08.634 align:middle line:84%
have become through the system
of capitalism and acquiring

00:16:08.634 --> 00:16:09.602 align:middle line:90%
of stuff.

00:16:09.602 --> 00:16:11.971 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually, we just
die and leave it behind.

00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:14.040 align:middle line:84%
And then what happens
to that stuff?

00:16:14.040 --> 00:16:16.809 align:middle line:84%
Somebody else is going to
acquire it from us and--

00:16:16.809 --> 00:16:19.445 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, not
just stuff but stature.

00:16:19.445 --> 00:16:22.381 align:middle line:84%
It has come down
to that, really.

00:16:22.381 --> 00:16:25.017 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when we're looking at
how we educate our children,

00:16:25.017 --> 00:16:27.687 align:middle line:84%
for example, which we'll be
getting into, a lot of it

00:16:27.687 --> 00:16:29.655 align:middle line:90%
is, oh, you must go to college.

00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:30.690 align:middle line:90%
You must have a college--

00:16:30.690 --> 00:16:32.892 align:middle line:84%
Well, now we're starting to
see the failings in that.

00:16:32.892 --> 00:16:36.963 align:middle line:84%
We have hundreds of thousands
of college graduates who

00:16:36.963 --> 00:16:39.632 align:middle line:84%
are vying for jobs in
the service industry

00:16:39.632 --> 00:16:42.268 align:middle line:84%
to get a job as a
waiter or a busser

00:16:42.268 --> 00:16:43.436 align:middle line:90%
at a restaurant or anything.

00:16:43.436 --> 00:16:45.104 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: It's all
smoke and mirrors.

00:16:45.104 --> 00:16:46.272 align:middle line:90%
It's all deception.

00:16:46.272 --> 00:16:48.341 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yet we all
fell into this trap

00:16:48.341 --> 00:16:51.143 align:middle line:84%
because somehow to
have any status in life

00:16:51.143 --> 00:16:52.879 align:middle line:84%
where you could
acquire what you wanted

00:16:52.879 --> 00:16:56.716 align:middle line:84%
or position yourself or have
freedom, latitude, freedom

00:16:56.716 --> 00:16:59.285 align:middle line:84%
of movement even,
required a certain income.

00:16:59.285 --> 00:17:01.754 align:middle line:84%
A certain income required a
certain level of education.

00:17:01.754 --> 00:17:04.757 align:middle line:84%
And it started really infecting
the thinking all the way up

00:17:04.757 --> 00:17:07.894 align:middle line:84%
the chain to where you're not
making any organically sound

00:17:07.894 --> 00:17:08.728 align:middle line:90%
decisions anymore.

00:17:08.728 --> 00:17:10.596 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: It's the
hierarchical structure.

00:17:10.596 --> 00:17:12.698 align:middle line:90%
It's the hierarchical pyramid.

00:17:12.698 --> 00:17:14.500 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, in
hierarchical pyramid,

00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:16.969 align:middle line:84%
there's only one person
who can be at the top.

00:17:16.969 --> 00:17:18.471 align:middle line:84%
And the rest of the
people are going

00:17:18.471 --> 00:17:20.406 align:middle line:84%
to have to work for that
one person at the top

00:17:20.406 --> 00:17:21.406 align:middle line:90%
and grovel their way up.

00:17:21.406 --> 00:17:23.675 align:middle line:84%
And somebody's always going
to try and push the one guy

00:17:23.675 --> 00:17:25.478 align:middle line:84%
off the top so they
can be at the top.

00:17:25.478 --> 00:17:29.015 align:middle line:84%
So let's just quickly examine
the fundamentals of this

00:17:29.015 --> 00:17:30.016 align:middle line:90%
because it's important.

00:17:30.016 --> 00:17:31.384 align:middle line:84%
Some people might
say, well, what

00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:32.518 align:middle line:90%
are you guys talking about?

00:17:32.518 --> 00:17:33.953 align:middle line:90%
You're going around and around.

00:17:33.953 --> 00:17:36.389 align:middle line:84%
Well, why are we
in this position?

00:17:36.389 --> 00:17:42.228 align:middle line:84%
Why are we in this horribly
confusing state of our species

00:17:42.228 --> 00:17:46.532 align:middle line:84%
that most people
hate their lives?

00:17:46.532 --> 00:17:47.733 align:middle line:90%
Most people hate their lives.

00:17:47.733 --> 00:17:48.467 align:middle line:90%
They hate their jobs.

00:17:48.467 --> 00:17:49.268 align:middle line:90%
They hate their boss.

00:17:49.268 --> 00:17:50.736 align:middle line:84%
They hate waking
up in the morning,

00:17:50.736 --> 00:17:53.706 align:middle line:84%
catching a train or a plane, or
riding a bicycle in the rain,

00:17:53.706 --> 00:17:55.641 align:middle line:90%
in the snow, having to drive.

00:17:55.641 --> 00:18:00.513 align:middle line:84%
And then in third world
countries, it's harsh.

00:18:00.513 --> 00:18:03.883 align:middle line:84%
But everybody has their
own personal misery

00:18:03.883 --> 00:18:05.284 align:middle line:90%
that they have to deal with.

00:18:05.284 --> 00:18:07.954 align:middle line:84%
They are not doing
what they believe

00:18:07.954 --> 00:18:09.689 align:middle line:90%
their natural talents are.

00:18:09.689 --> 00:18:11.324 align:middle line:84%
They're not sharing
the energy that

00:18:11.324 --> 00:18:13.559 align:middle line:84%
comes from within with
the rest of the world.

00:18:13.559 --> 00:18:17.063 align:middle line:84%
They're doing something
else that they hate to do

00:18:17.063 --> 00:18:20.232 align:middle line:84%
and they're forced to do to
earn a few lousy bucks so

00:18:20.232 --> 00:18:22.568 align:middle line:84%
at the end of the month they
can buy some bread and milk

00:18:22.568 --> 00:18:25.171 align:middle line:84%
and pay for the electricity
that should be free.

00:18:25.171 --> 00:18:26.739 align:middle line:84%
But we're paying
through our noses

00:18:26.739 --> 00:18:29.508 align:middle line:84%
to get electricity and send
the children to school.

00:18:29.508 --> 00:18:32.445 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, they're going
to struggle through life.

00:18:32.445 --> 00:18:35.481 align:middle line:84%
So it's this never-ending
cycle of chasing your tail

00:18:35.481 --> 00:18:39.218 align:middle line:84%
to earn a few bucks so
you can live and survive.

00:18:39.218 --> 00:18:41.687 align:middle line:90%
Well, why is that happening?

00:18:44.490 --> 00:18:48.194 align:middle line:84%
Every socio-political system
we've had as a species

00:18:48.194 --> 00:18:49.528 align:middle line:90%
has failed us.

00:18:49.528 --> 00:18:51.230 align:middle line:84%
It's failed us for
specific reasons.

00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:53.199 align:middle line:84%
We probably don't have
enough time to go into--

00:18:53.199 --> 00:18:54.633 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To go into all of
them or any of them really.

00:18:54.633 --> 00:18:55.468 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: --that.

00:18:55.468 --> 00:18:56.302 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:18:56.302 --> 00:18:59.105 align:middle line:84%
And I'm talking about
capitalism, communism,

00:18:59.105 --> 00:19:00.906 align:middle line:90%
socialism, fascism.

00:19:00.906 --> 00:19:03.042 align:middle line:90%
You call it whatever you want.

00:19:03.042 --> 00:19:04.977 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes
people get confused

00:19:04.977 --> 00:19:06.846 align:middle line:84%
when I talk about
contributionism.

00:19:06.846 --> 00:19:08.314 align:middle line:90%
It's another ism.

00:19:08.314 --> 00:19:10.616 align:middle line:84%
I don't really like the
fact that it's an ism.

00:19:10.616 --> 00:19:14.453 align:middle line:84%
But it's a nice ism because
it's completely and utterly

00:19:14.453 --> 00:19:17.423 align:middle line:84%
different from every
other ism we've had,

00:19:17.423 --> 00:19:19.892 align:middle line:84%
because every other ism
we've had as a species

00:19:19.892 --> 00:19:24.430 align:middle line:84%
was always based on
one thing, money.

00:19:24.430 --> 00:19:28.834 align:middle line:84%
Contributionism is a system
that works without money.

00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:31.570 align:middle line:84%
And the fundamentals
are really simple.

00:19:31.570 --> 00:19:33.239 align:middle line:84%
Some people still
believe that money

00:19:33.239 --> 00:19:35.941 align:middle line:84%
is a consequence of
natural evolution,

00:19:35.941 --> 00:19:39.278 align:middle line:84%
that we had barter and
trade, and then they

00:19:39.278 --> 00:19:42.515 align:middle line:84%
became promissory notes, and
then they became minted coins.

00:19:42.515 --> 00:19:44.183 align:middle line:90%
That is not true.

00:19:44.183 --> 00:19:45.317 align:middle line:90%
That's the lie.

00:19:45.317 --> 00:19:48.621 align:middle line:84%
And those are the deceptions
that we've been told and taught

00:19:48.621 --> 00:19:50.990 align:middle line:84%
so that we think it's
OK to have money.

00:19:50.990 --> 00:19:52.525 align:middle line:84%
Well, no, it's not
OK to have money.

00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:54.360 align:middle line:90%
We don't need money.

00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:56.462 align:middle line:90%
Money does nothing.

00:19:56.462 --> 00:19:58.230 align:middle line:90%
People do everything.

00:19:58.230 --> 00:19:59.498 align:middle line:90%
People plant the seeds.

00:19:59.498 --> 00:20:00.866 align:middle line:90%
People grow the food.

00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:03.602 align:middle line:84%
People solve the
mathematical solutions.

00:20:03.602 --> 00:20:05.438 align:middle line:90%
People look after babies.

00:20:05.438 --> 00:20:08.040 align:middle line:84%
People develop the rockets
and the technology.

00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:09.575 align:middle line:90%
Money does nothing.

00:20:09.575 --> 00:20:13.412 align:middle line:84%
Money is the hurdle between
abundance and success

00:20:13.412 --> 00:20:17.283 align:middle line:90%
on all levels or failure.

00:20:17.283 --> 00:20:20.119 align:middle line:84%
So if we want
success in abundance

00:20:20.119 --> 00:20:22.354 align:middle line:84%
and have as much food and
abundance on all level,

00:20:22.354 --> 00:20:25.558 align:middle line:84%
whether it's food or
technology or rocket science

00:20:25.558 --> 00:20:29.261 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is your
mind can conjure up,

00:20:29.261 --> 00:20:31.097 align:middle line:84%
the moment you remove
money from the system,

00:20:31.097 --> 00:20:34.033 align:middle line:84%
you open the floodgates
to absolute abundance

00:20:34.033 --> 00:20:34.834 align:middle line:90%
on every level.

00:20:34.834 --> 00:20:36.535 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And essentially,
as soon as you

00:20:36.535 --> 00:20:39.405 align:middle line:84%
do that, a feeling
of equality starts

00:20:39.405 --> 00:20:41.207 align:middle line:84%
happening within the
hearts of individuals.

00:20:41.207 --> 00:20:42.475 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: And so it should.

00:20:42.475 --> 00:20:44.343 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and it
should, absolutely.

00:20:44.343 --> 00:20:45.411 align:middle line:90%
That's our natural state.

00:20:45.411 --> 00:20:47.513 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: We're all
told, we're all born equal.

00:20:47.513 --> 00:20:49.949 align:middle line:84%
Well, for a millisecond
we're all equal.

00:20:49.949 --> 00:20:50.883 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:20:50.883 --> 00:20:53.786 align:middle line:84%
And then that inequality
starts, and it just

00:20:53.786 --> 00:20:55.821 align:middle line:84%
gets worse and
worse until you die.

00:20:55.821 --> 00:20:57.756 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, we're
all equal but different.

