basic necessities: food, water,

00:26:34.860 --> 00:26:42.100 align:middle line:84%
housing, shelter, health care,
education-- the fundamentals

00:26:42.100 --> 00:26:44.837 align:middle line:84%
that every society
and community needs.

00:26:44.837 --> 00:26:47.139 align:middle line:90%
So let's start with the food.

00:26:47.139 --> 00:26:49.374 align:middle line:84%
The food and water is
the most important thing.

00:26:49.374 --> 00:26:55.113 align:middle line:84%
So farmers will play a key
role in the transition phase

00:26:55.113 --> 00:26:58.584 align:middle line:84%
into moneyless societies
because once a community's got

00:26:58.584 --> 00:27:02.421 align:middle line:84%
enough food and
water, they can start

00:27:02.421 --> 00:27:03.722 align:middle line:90%
thinking about everything else.

00:27:03.722 --> 00:27:05.457 align:middle line:84%
They don't have to
worry about, where

00:27:05.457 --> 00:27:07.860 align:middle line:84%
am I going to earn enough
money to buy some food?

00:27:07.860 --> 00:27:08.527 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:27:08.527 --> 00:27:10.329 align:middle line:84%
You have your basic
survival needs.

00:27:10.329 --> 00:27:12.397 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: And if the
community looks after each

00:27:12.397 --> 00:27:15.934 align:middle line:84%
other with food, and you
have the people within that

00:27:15.934 --> 00:27:19.104 align:middle line:84%
community that are really the
good cooks and the chefs--

00:27:19.104 --> 00:27:21.139 align:middle line:90%
I'm really simplifying it now.

00:27:21.139 --> 00:27:23.709 align:middle line:10%
--that provide the food,
that cook the food so

00:27:23.709 --> 00:27:25.477 align:middle line:10%
that the whole
community can eat,

00:27:25.477 --> 00:27:29.214 align:middle line:10%
and now you've got some
serious solutions to,

00:27:29.214 --> 00:27:30.616 align:middle line:10%
especially in
Africa, where you've

00:27:30.616 --> 00:27:33.886 align:middle line:10%
got a lot of homelessness, a
lot of hunger because there's

00:27:33.886 --> 00:27:38.924 align:middle line:10%
no jobs, and people spend all
their time and energy to earn

00:27:38.924 --> 00:27:41.627 align:middle line:10%
a few bucks,
whether it's begging

00:27:41.627 --> 00:27:44.463 align:middle line:10%
or whether it's coming to
you for a job every day

00:27:44.463 --> 00:27:47.299 align:middle line:10%
so they can earn a
few rands or dollars

00:27:47.299 --> 00:27:48.934 align:middle line:10%
so they can go buy some food.

00:27:48.934 --> 00:27:53.372 align:middle line:84%
Well, if they spend that time on
community projects, developing

00:27:53.372 --> 00:27:56.074 align:middle line:84%
food, everybody can have
food in that community.

00:27:56.074 --> 00:27:58.710 align:middle line:90%
So let's backtrack a little bit.

00:27:58.710 --> 00:28:01.179 align:middle line:84%
The most important thing that
these communities need to do,

00:28:01.179 --> 00:28:03.248 align:middle line:84%
the small towns,
is start working

00:28:03.248 --> 00:28:05.350 align:middle line:84%
with the farmers
around the areas,

00:28:05.350 --> 00:28:09.755 align:middle line:84%
and whether it's growing food
or dairy farms or chickens

00:28:09.755 --> 00:28:13.825 align:middle line:84%
and eggs, and then
extending that into things

00:28:13.825 --> 00:28:17.329 align:middle line:84%
like converting the sewage
plants into free energy,

00:28:17.329 --> 00:28:20.399 align:middle line:84%
methane gas, and
using the rivers

00:28:20.399 --> 00:28:22.834 align:middle line:84%
and solar to generate
energy so you

