to build houses that are
far more eco-friendly.

00:29:00.138 --> 00:29:02.007 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: More
insulated for example.

00:29:02.007 --> 00:29:02.708 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yes.

00:29:02.708 --> 00:29:04.843 align:middle line:84%
You look at houses that
are 2,000 years old

00:29:04.843 --> 00:29:07.546 align:middle line:84%
built in the Near East,
and they're standing.

00:29:07.546 --> 00:29:10.282 align:middle line:84%
You look at a house that's 100
years old standing around here,

00:29:10.282 --> 00:29:11.750 align:middle line:90%
they're broken down.

00:29:11.750 --> 00:29:13.952 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It takes
a fire all around.

00:29:13.952 --> 00:29:17.222 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: And so
imagine if you've

00:29:17.222 --> 00:29:19.424 align:middle line:84%
got this little community
that get together.

00:29:19.424 --> 00:29:21.526 align:middle line:84%
They decide, right, this
is what we're going to do.

00:29:21.526 --> 00:29:22.995 align:middle line:84%
We're going to look
after ourselves

00:29:22.995 --> 00:29:27.265 align:middle line:84%
in all these obvious areas--
energy, food, water, shelter,

00:29:27.265 --> 00:29:30.068 align:middle line:84%
housing-- and then
use that as a base

00:29:30.068 --> 00:29:35.207 align:middle line:90%
to expand that to other areas.

00:29:35.207 --> 00:29:37.542 align:middle line:84%
So very shortly, you're going
to have a community that's

00:29:37.542 --> 00:29:41.747 align:middle line:84%
going to be living virtually
free because they're paying

00:29:41.747 --> 00:29:43.548 align:middle line:84%
very little for energy
and electricity.--

00:29:43.548 --> 00:29:45.417 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're using
their natural resources.

00:29:45.417 --> 00:29:46.184 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yeah.

00:29:46.184 --> 00:29:48.520 align:middle line:84%
They've got bread
and milk and butter

00:29:48.520 --> 00:29:51.089 align:middle line:84%
that they make available for all
the people in their community

00:29:51.089 --> 00:29:53.592 align:middle line:84%
because they're
contributing to making it.

00:29:53.592 --> 00:29:57.396 align:middle line:84%
And you know how much you can
make, how much milk and stuff

00:29:57.396 --> 00:29:59.097 align:middle line:84%
you can generate with
very little effort

00:29:59.097 --> 00:30:00.832 align:middle line:90%
if you really apply yourself.

00:30:00.832 --> 00:30:04.002 align:middle line:84%
So now, suddenly everyone's got
everything in that community.

00:30:04.002 --> 00:30:05.771 align:middle line:84%
What's the next
step that happens.

00:30:05.771 --> 00:30:08.573 align:middle line:84%
The next step is now, OK,
you've got too much stuff,

00:30:08.573 --> 00:30:11.143 align:middle line:84%
because that's what happens
when you do what you love to do

00:30:11.143 --> 00:30:12.778 align:middle line:84%
and if you're looking
after each other.

00:30:12.778 --> 00:30:13.845 align:middle line:90%
You've got too much stuff.

00:30:13.845 --> 00:30:15.647 align:middle line:84%
So you're going to
start making the stuff

00:30:15.647 --> 00:30:19.217 align:middle line:84%
available to the
communities around you

00:30:19.217 --> 00:30:21.253 align:middle line:84%
at a fraction of the
price that they're

00:30:21.253 --> 00:30:23.588 align:middle line:90%
buying it at the supermarket.

00:30:23.588 --> 00:30:24.956 align:middle line:84%
So all the
communities around you

00:30:24.956 --> 00:30:27.459 align:middle line:84%
are going to start coming to
you to buy their milk and bread

00:30:27.459 --> 00:30:29.728 align:middle line:90%
and butter and all the stuff.

00:30:29.728 --> 00:30:33.065 align:middle line:84%
What's going to happen to
their own communities is

00:30:33.065 --> 00:30:34.466 align:middle line:90%
they're going to say, hold on.

00:30:34.466 --> 00:30:36.702 align:middle line:84%
We can't survive doing
the business the way

00:30:36.702 --> 00:30:39.404 align:middle line:84%
we used to because all
the people from our town

00:30:39.404 --> 00:30:42.140 align:middle line:84%
are getting their stuff
from the neighboring town.

00:30:42.140 --> 00:30:45.610 align:middle line:84%
So that's going to force them
to take on the same model

00:30:45.610 --> 00:30:47.779 align:middle line:84%
and looking after each
other so they can also

00:30:47.779 --> 00:30:50.382 align:middle line:84%
live virtually free
and creating abundance

00:30:50.382 --> 00:30:52.651 align:middle line:90%
of the basic necessities.

00:30:52.651 --> 00:30:56.688 align:middle line:84%
Now, you've got the people that
have got all this extra time.

00:30:56.688 --> 00:30:59.691 align:middle line:84%
Now, they can start looking
at beautifying the town

00:30:59.691 --> 00:31:04.730 align:middle line:84%
and building free energy
devices and developing

00:31:04.730 --> 00:31:09.801 align:middle line:84%
the civil engineering, solving
solutions with sewage problems

00:31:09.801 --> 00:31:14.439 align:middle line:84%
and developing arts and
recreational facilities.

00:31:14.439 --> 00:31:17.476 align:middle line:84%
And that's the spark that
gets this thing going

00:31:17.476 --> 00:31:19.945 align:middle line:90%
to every level of society.

00:31:19.945 --> 00:31:22.314 align:middle line:84%
Shoemakers are making
beautiful shoes.

00:31:22.314 --> 00:31:24.449 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly everybody
wants to come and get

00:31:24.449 --> 00:31:25.450 align:middle line:90%
the shoes from this guy.

00:31:25.450 --> 00:31:27.085 align:middle line:84%
And where does he
get the leather from?

00:31:27.085 --> 00:31:29.221 align:middle line:84%
Well, from the guys that
are running the farms that

00:31:29.221 --> 00:31:33.225 align:middle line:84%
providing the meat and the
cows and all that stuff.

00:31:33.225 --> 00:31:37.262 align:middle line:84%
So you start seeing how this
integrated structure can

00:31:37.262 --> 00:31:40.232 align:middle line:84%
happen very, very quickly
in the small towns

00:31:40.232 --> 00:31:42.167 align:middle line:84%
and create the
domino effect that

00:31:42.167 --> 00:31:46.071 align:middle line:84%
get all the other small towns
to respond the same way.

00:31:46.071 --> 00:31:48.173 align:middle line:84%
Once that happens, I think
it's a runaway train.

00:31:48.173 --> 00:31:48.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, OK.

00:31:48.940 --> 00:31:51.042 align:middle line:84%
Now, let me ask you,
devil's advocate.

00:31:51.042 --> 00:31:53.278 align:middle line:84%
If anybody out there is
thinking, but, wait a minute.

00:31:53.278 --> 00:31:56.348 align:middle line:84%
We always hear these
tales of our grandparents,

00:31:56.348 --> 00:31:59.351 align:middle line:84%
who worked the land and
that they worked from sunup

00:31:59.351 --> 00:32:04.489 align:middle line:84%
to sundown trying to make
a profit from the land.

00:32:04.489 --> 00:32:06.491 align:middle line:90%
Now, where is it--

00:32:06.491 --> 00:32:08.026 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: The
key word was profit.

00:32:08.026 --> 00:32:09.094 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The key
word was profit.

00:32:09.094 --> 00:32:09.594 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:32:09.594 --> 00:32:10.028 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: You see, profit.

00:32:10.028 --> 00:32:12.330 align:middle line:84%
You take profit out of
it, it changes everything.

00:32:12.330 --> 00:32:14.266 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because they're
making huge amounts.

00:32:14.266 --> 00:32:16.368 align:middle line:84%
I mean, obviously
they're producing food

00:32:16.368 --> 00:32:17.936 align:middle line:84%
to feed a lot of
other individuals.

00:32:17.936 --> 00:32:19.771 align:middle line:84%
And that's the way they
would make a profit.

00:32:19.771 --> 00:32:21.873 align:middle line:10%
So where in this model
would you say, no,

00:32:21.873 --> 00:32:23.508 align:middle line:10%
this is not idealistic.

00:32:23.508 --> 00:32:25.744 align:middle line:10%
What you're talking
about is not idealistic.

00:32:25.744 --> 00:32:30.015 align:middle line:10%
You don't have to work your
little heiny off from sunup

00:32:30.015 --> 00:32:30.749 align:middle line:10%
to sundown.

00:32:30.749 --> 00:32:31.483 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yeah.

00:32:31.483 --> 00:32:34.085 align:middle line:90%
So I always tell people--

00:32:34.085 --> 00:32:35.754 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, this
is a long discussion

00:32:35.754 --> 00:32:39.057 align:middle line:84%
because this isn't something
that I put together

00:32:39.057 --> 00:32:40.091 align:middle line:90%
over the last few weeks.

00:32:40.091 --> 00:32:43.528 align:middle line:84%
This has taken me many
years to put together.

00:32:43.528 --> 00:32:45.831 align:middle line:84%
And going through
every aspect of it

00:32:45.831 --> 00:32:48.200 align:middle line:84%
and realizing, as I mentioned
earlier, how simple it is.

00:32:48.200 --> 00:32:51.236 align:middle line:84%
Once you break through some of
the real barriers that we have,

00:32:51.236 --> 00:32:53.071 align:middle line:90%
you realize how simple it is.

00:32:53.071 --> 00:32:54.873 align:middle line:84%
Some people call
it utopian dreams.

00:32:54.873 --> 00:32:56.041 align:middle line:90%
And I say no, no, no.

00:32:56.041 --> 00:32:57.409 align:middle line:90%
It's not utopian dreams.

00:32:57.409 --> 00:33:00.445 align:middle line:84%
It's the natural
order of things.

00:33:00.445 --> 00:33:02.380 align:middle line:90%
It's the way that nature works.

00:33:02.380 --> 00:33:04.549 align:middle line:84%
We're just following the
natural order of things,

00:33:04.549 --> 00:33:08.053 align:middle line:84%
and for that reason it's
virtually infallible.

00:33:08.053 --> 00:33:10.989 align:middle line:90%
It's a self-correcting system.

00:33:10.989 --> 00:33:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And if you allow it to work,
utilizing the natural order

00:33:15.760 --> 00:33:16.361 align:middle line:90%
of things--

00:33:16.361 --> 00:33:18.296 align:middle line:84%
And again, there are
many other things

00:33:18.296 --> 00:33:20.999 align:middle line:84%
that I need to throw into the
pot to explain what I'm saying.

00:33:20.999 --> 00:33:22.334 align:middle line:90%
It's a self-correcting system.

00:33:22.334 --> 00:33:25.070 align:middle line:84%
Every problem area
within that community,

00:33:25.070 --> 00:33:27.072 align:middle line:84%
the Ubuntu
contributionist community

00:33:27.072 --> 00:33:31.042 align:middle line:84%
that runs without
money, corrects itself

00:33:31.042 --> 00:33:33.778 align:middle line:84%
because you always ask
the questions, well,

00:33:33.778 --> 00:33:36.014 align:middle line:84%
how does it benefit all the
people in the community?

00:33:36.014 --> 00:33:38.116 align:middle line:84%
If it doesn't benefit the
people in the community,

00:33:38.116 --> 00:33:40.886 align:middle line:84%
then it's not necessary
for the community.

00:33:40.886 --> 00:33:41.887 align:middle line:90%
We can have it.

00:33:41.887 --> 00:33:42.654 align:middle line:90%
We can use it.

00:33:42.654 --> 00:33:46.057 align:middle line:84%
But then it's not part of
the fundamental structure

00:33:46.057 --> 00:33:48.760 align:middle line:90%
that the community works toward.

00:33:48.760 --> 00:33:50.128 align:middle line:90%
It is an add-on.

00:33:50.128 --> 00:33:52.397 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing
wrong with add-ons.

00:33:52.397 --> 00:33:53.632 align:middle line:90%
What happens with add-ons--

00:33:53.632 --> 00:33:56.835 align:middle line:84%
And now, I'm getting into the
really exciting part of it.

00:33:56.835 --> 00:33:59.571 align:middle line:84%
--what happens, now you were
living in this community.

00:33:59.571 --> 00:34:02.874 align:middle line:84%
You wake up in the morning
with a smile on your face

00:34:02.874 --> 00:34:06.278 align:middle line:84%
because what you go and
do is what you love to do.

00:34:06.278 --> 00:34:07.746 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this
dynamic itself

00:34:07.746 --> 00:34:10.047 align:middle line:84%
changes the entire
equation because you're

00:34:10.047 --> 00:34:14.619 align:middle line:84%
taking fully participatory
human creativity and energy.

00:34:14.619 --> 00:34:15.987 align:middle line:90%
You don't even need discipline.

00:34:15.987 --> 00:34:17.554 align:middle line:84%
Discipline doesn't
exist when people

00:34:17.554 --> 00:34:19.157 align:middle line:90%
are doing what they love to do.

00:34:19.157 --> 00:34:20.391 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't require discipline.

00:34:20.391 --> 00:34:20.891 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: And
you're not doing it

00:34:20.891 --> 00:34:21.693 align:middle line:84%
because you're
earning money for it.

00:34:21.693 --> 00:34:22.960 align:middle line:84%
You're doing it because
you love to do it.

00:34:22.960 --> 00:34:24.963 align:middle line:84%
And you choose to do
it for your community.

00:34:24.963 --> 00:34:27.766 align:middle line:84%
Again, there's a
process of how you

00:34:27.766 --> 00:34:30.201 align:middle line:84%
get appointed to do
that by your community.

00:34:30.201 --> 00:34:32.637 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that the community
has allowed you or chosen

00:34:32.637 --> 00:34:33.972 align:middle line:90%
you to do what that is.

00:34:33.972 --> 00:34:36.007 align:middle line:84%
Whether you're a
shoemaker, a glass blower,

00:34:36.007 --> 00:34:39.244 align:middle line:84%
or a farmer or a
rocket scientist,

00:34:39.244 --> 00:34:41.212 align:middle line:84%
depending on what
community you live in,

00:34:41.212 --> 00:34:42.813 align:middle line:90%
or a teacher or whatever--

00:34:42.813 --> 00:34:45.650 align:middle line:84%
Master teachers, but that's
a whole separate subject

00:34:45.650 --> 00:34:46.952 align:middle line:90%
altogether.

00:34:46.952 --> 00:34:48.820 align:middle line:90%
Teaching changes dramatically.

00:34:48.820 --> 00:34:50.455 align:middle line:84%
--and so you wake
up in the morning.

00:34:50.455 --> 00:34:53.024 align:middle line:84%
And you might just be the
chemical engineer that's

00:34:53.024 --> 00:34:55.360 align:middle line:84%
waking up, and you've
just figured out

00:34:55.360 --> 00:34:57.896 align:middle line:84%
how you're going to solve
the problem of sewage.

00:34:57.896 --> 00:34:58.463 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:34:58.463 --> 00:35:00.632 align:middle line:84%
And I'm using this
as a wild card idea.

00:35:00.632 --> 00:35:03.034 align:middle line:84%
So you're going to be
so excited about this,

00:35:03.034 --> 00:35:06.271 align:middle line:84%
you're going to run off to your
work or what it is you do--

00:35:06.271 --> 00:35:07.605 align:middle line:90%
You're no longer working.

00:35:07.605 --> 00:35:09.374 align:middle line:84%
You're following
your labor of love.

00:35:09.374 --> 00:35:11.276 align:middle line:84%
So jobs and work
are words that are

00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.711 align:middle line:84%
going to disappear
because now it's

00:35:12.711 --> 00:35:15.647 align:middle line:84%
a labor of love, an
LOL, which you're

00:35:15.647 --> 00:35:18.316 align:middle line:84%
going to do with a
smile on your face,

00:35:18.316 --> 00:35:20.085 align:middle line:84%
laughing out loud
while you're working.

00:35:20.085 --> 00:35:22.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And people have
forgotten what they love.

00:35:22.220 --> 00:35:23.221 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yes.

00:35:23.221 --> 00:35:25.156 align:middle line:90%
So there's no bad energy.

00:35:25.156 --> 00:35:26.624 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is
you're doing, you're

00:35:26.624 --> 00:35:27.993 align:middle line:90%
putting all your good energy.

00:35:27.993 --> 00:35:29.661 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's baking
bread, can you

00:35:29.661 --> 00:35:32.330 align:middle line:84%
imagine how much good energy
is in the bread that'll

00:35:32.330 --> 00:35:33.732 align:middle line:90%
come out of the bakeries?

00:35:33.732 --> 00:35:36.267 align:middle line:84%
And how much love is going to
be in the cheese and the butter

00:35:36.267 --> 00:35:37.535 align:middle line:90%
and the woodwork factories?

00:35:37.535 --> 00:35:39.037 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You can
already experience

00:35:39.037 --> 00:35:41.006 align:middle line:84%
that in places that
operate off this principle.

00:35:41.006 --> 00:35:41.406 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:35:41.406 --> 00:35:42.874 align:middle line:84%
And remember,
everything is energy.

00:35:42.874 --> 00:35:45.677 align:middle line:84%
If you hate your job, and
you do whatever it is,

00:35:45.677 --> 00:35:48.480 align:middle line:84%
and you do it because you're
going to earn some lousy bucks,

00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.081 align:middle line:84%
and you hate it,
you hate your boss,

00:35:50.081 --> 00:35:55.253 align:middle line:84%
you hate the whole process,
that's a recipe for disaster.

00:35:55.253 --> 00:35:58.123 align:middle line:84%
If everybody does
this, let's quickly

00:35:58.123 --> 00:35:59.591 align:middle line:90%
look at what happens today.

00:35:59.591 --> 00:36:03.728 align:middle line:84%
90% of the time that people
spend during their day

00:36:03.728 --> 00:36:05.130 align:middle line:90%
is chasing money.

00:36:05.130 --> 00:36:07.499 align:middle line:84%
If you backtrack
and you analyze what

00:36:07.499 --> 00:36:09.434 align:middle line:84%
it is that I've
done today, you'll

00:36:09.434 --> 00:36:12.203 align:middle line:84%
realize that most of the
things you do, 90% of the time,

00:36:12.203 --> 00:36:15.206 align:middle line:84%
is actions that you've
taken to chase money

00:36:15.206 --> 00:36:17.776 align:middle line:84%
so that at the end of the
day you've earned some money.

00:36:17.776 --> 00:36:19.511 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you're not
doing that, now you're

00:36:19.511 --> 00:36:22.447 align:middle line:84%
spending 90% of
your time on things

00:36:22.447 --> 00:36:24.749 align:middle line:84%
you love to do for
your community that

00:36:24.749 --> 00:36:28.186 align:middle line:84%
benefits your community
and, therefore, benefits you

00:36:28.186 --> 00:36:29.220 align:middle line:90%
personally.

00:36:29.220 --> 00:36:30.722 align:middle line:90%
What happens?

00:36:30.722 --> 00:36:32.857 align:middle line:84%
If everybody does
that, that now it

00:36:32.857 --> 00:36:34.526 align:middle line:84%
means that you're
living in a community.

00:36:34.526 --> 00:36:36.027 align:middle line:90%
You're not sitting in traffic.

00:36:36.027 --> 00:36:36.528 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:36:36.528 --> 00:36:40.331 align:middle line:84%
You live where you work, where
you do what you love to do.

00:36:40.331 --> 00:36:42.700 align:middle line:84%
So now people can
live out of the cities

00:36:42.700 --> 00:36:44.569 align:middle line:84%
in the small little
villages that they

00:36:44.569 --> 00:36:46.404 align:middle line:90%
have a country cottage in.

00:36:46.404 --> 00:36:48.673 align:middle line:84%
That they're working all
week so they can get away

00:36:48.673 --> 00:36:51.609 align:middle line:84%
for the weekend to go and
spend a few lousy hours

00:36:51.609 --> 00:36:52.677 align:middle line:90%
in their country cottage.

00:36:52.677 --> 00:36:55.013 align:middle line:84%
Now, they can stay
there forever.

00:36:55.013 --> 00:36:59.551 align:middle line:84%
So what happens when you wake up
and you do your labor of love?

00:36:59.551 --> 00:37:01.619 align:middle line:84%
You can only do it
for a few hours a day.

00:37:01.619 --> 00:37:03.955 align:middle line:84%
And I use three
hours as an example

00:37:03.955 --> 00:37:06.091 align:middle line:84%
because it's the Holy
Trinity, and I like that.

00:37:06.091 --> 00:37:06.591 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:37:06.591 --> 00:37:09.360 align:middle line:84%
So three hours, the
holy trinity of time

00:37:09.360 --> 00:37:10.829 align:middle line:84%
that you spend
every day doing what

00:37:10.829 --> 00:37:12.597 align:middle line:90%
you love for your community.

00:37:12.597 --> 00:37:14.499 align:middle line:84%
If you do any more
than that, there'll

00:37:14.499 --> 00:37:16.468 align:middle line:90%
just be too much stuff.

00:37:16.468 --> 00:37:19.337 align:middle line:84%
There'll be too much food, too
much water, too much rocket

00:37:19.337 --> 00:37:21.206 align:middle line:90%
science, too much free energy.

00:37:21.206 --> 00:37:24.909 align:middle line:84%
