is taking the young children
at the earliest of ages,

00:46:16.941 --> 00:46:19.477 align:middle line:84%
probably between the ages
of four, five, and six,

00:46:19.477 --> 00:46:21.979 align:middle line:84%
and the first
fundamental principles

00:46:21.979 --> 00:46:23.748 align:middle line:84%
is teaching them
the love for Mother

00:46:23.748 --> 00:46:25.650 align:middle line:90%
Earth, the love for Gaia.

00:46:25.650 --> 00:46:27.918 align:middle line:84%
Once they have the love for
Gaia and they understand

00:46:27.918 --> 00:46:31.288 align:middle line:84%
some of the fundamentals of
how water and soil works, how

00:46:31.288 --> 00:46:36.861 align:middle line:84%
to grow seeds, and some of the
real basics, nature, earth,

00:46:36.861 --> 00:46:38.863 align:middle line:84%
natural environment,
they will never

00:46:38.863 --> 00:46:41.632 align:middle line:84%
hurt our mother,
Mother Earth, Gaia.

00:46:41.632 --> 00:46:45.002 align:middle line:84%
And that's, for me, the
fundamental starting point.

00:46:45.002 --> 00:46:48.372 align:middle line:84%
From there, you're
growing conscious beings

00:46:48.372 --> 00:46:50.307 align:middle line:84%
that will always be
responsible and feel

00:46:50.307 --> 00:46:52.677 align:middle line:84%
responsible for what
it is that they do.

00:46:52.677 --> 00:46:56.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, the education system
is really, really important

00:46:56.080 --> 00:46:58.382 align:middle line:84%
because it lies at
the foundation of how

00:46:58.382 --> 00:47:01.686 align:middle line:84%
the future civilizations
are going to act and behave.

00:47:01.686 --> 00:47:04.221 align:middle line:84%
And this is why this
system is so beautiful.

00:47:04.221 --> 00:47:06.724 align:middle line:84%
Remember, I said it's a
self-correcting system?

00:47:06.724 --> 00:47:09.827 align:middle line:84%
And before we talk about how
the education system will work--

00:47:09.827 --> 00:47:10.995 align:middle line:90%
Well, let's talk about that.

00:47:10.995 --> 00:47:11.495 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:47:11.495 --> 00:47:13.264 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise,
I'm jumping around.

00:47:13.264 --> 00:47:14.699 align:middle line:90%
So there are no classrooms.

00:47:14.699 --> 00:47:16.333 align:middle line:90%
Forget it.

00:47:16.333 --> 00:47:18.769 align:middle line:90%
There are master teachers.

00:47:18.769 --> 00:47:20.271 align:middle line:90%
Who are master teachers?

00:47:20.271 --> 00:47:22.339 align:middle line:84%
Master teachers can
only be a master teacher

00:47:22.339 --> 00:47:25.209 align:middle line:84%
if they were appointed
by the community

00:47:25.209 --> 00:47:26.677 align:middle line:90%
to be a master teacher.

00:47:26.677 --> 00:47:31.082 align:middle line:84%
Whether you're a shoemaker,
a baker, a farmer, a rocket

00:47:31.082 --> 00:47:33.884 align:middle line:84%
scientist, whatever
it is that you do,

00:47:33.884 --> 00:47:37.755 align:middle line:84%
a sculptor, right,
only the community

00:47:37.755 --> 00:47:40.791 align:middle line:84%
can say Regina is
a master sculptor.

00:47:40.791 --> 00:47:43.260 align:middle line:90%
We've appointed her as such.

00:47:43.260 --> 00:47:45.830 align:middle line:84%
And then the children
will come to you

00:47:45.830 --> 00:47:48.833 align:middle line:90%
to learn a process as they grow.

00:47:48.833 --> 00:47:50.601 align:middle line:84%
After they've learned
the love for Gaia,

00:47:50.601 --> 00:47:55.239 align:middle line:84%
they go through a sequence
of workshops and internships,

00:47:55.239 --> 00:47:56.640 align:middle line:90%
little mini internships--

00:47:56.640 --> 00:47:59.477 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, are these
based on their own loves,

00:47:59.477 --> 00:48:03.247 align:middle line:84%
their own intrigues
and curiosities?

00:48:03.247 --> 00:48:07.718 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: It starts off with
basic needs of community, which

00:48:07.718 --> 00:48:13.691 align:middle line:84%
is food, water, shelter, health,
the basic needs of community.

00:48:13.691 --> 00:48:16.393 align:middle line:84%
So the children will be
introduced from a young age

00:48:16.393 --> 00:48:17.461 align:middle line:90%
into one day.

00:48:17.461 --> 00:48:21.165 align:middle line:84%
So one day they'll go and learn
how the farmer milks the cow.

00:48:21.165 --> 00:48:23.901 align:middle line:84%
The next day they'll go and
learn how cheese is made.

00:48:23.901 --> 00:48:24.835 align:middle line:90%
The next day--

00:48:24.835 --> 00:48:27.071 align:middle line:84%
So every day they
learn something new.

00:48:27.071 --> 00:48:29.206 align:middle line:84%
So they become one
day little internships

00:48:29.206 --> 00:48:30.174 align:middle line:90%
for the young children.

00:48:30.174 --> 00:48:31.709 align:middle line:84%
Then they become
two day internships.

00:48:31.709 --> 00:48:34.745 align:middle line:84%
Then they become three day,
four day, a week internship.

00:48:34.745 --> 00:48:37.615 align:middle line:84%
By the time a child
is 10 or 12 years old,

00:48:37.615 --> 00:48:40.184 align:middle line:84%
they become maybe a month
internship or two week

00:48:40.184 --> 00:48:40.785 align:middle line:90%
internships.

00:48:40.785 --> 00:48:44.021 align:middle line:84%
You learn everything from
the basic farming stuff

00:48:44.021 --> 00:48:48.959 align:middle line:84%
to woodwork to welding
to mechanical stuff

00:48:48.959 --> 00:48:53.731 align:middle line:84%
to electronic stuff to rocket
science to nuclear science

00:48:53.731 --> 00:48:55.099 align:middle line:90%
to you name it.

00:48:55.099 --> 00:48:56.567 align:middle line:90%
You will do that internship.

00:48:56.567 --> 00:48:58.235 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And there
are sort of examples

00:48:58.235 --> 00:48:59.904 align:middle line:84%
of this that are
going on right now.

00:48:59.904 --> 00:49:01.906 align:middle line:84%
You and I talked
about this off camera.

00:49:01.906 --> 00:49:03.941 align:middle line:84%
There is a school,
a model for this.

00:49:03.941 --> 00:49:06.143 align:middle line:84%
Have you read the
Anastasia series of books?

00:49:06.143 --> 00:49:07.144 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: I
haven't read them all.

00:49:07.144 --> 00:49:08.579 align:middle line:84%
But I'm familiar
with the content.

00:49:08.579 --> 00:49:10.915 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So-- but we've
talked about this off camera.

00:49:10.915 --> 00:49:12.850 align:middle line:84%
We were talking
about a school they

00:49:12.850 --> 00:49:14.885 align:middle line:84%
have there, in which the
kids learn in this way.

00:49:14.885 --> 00:49:17.321 align:middle line:84%
They learn in blocks, where
there are no teachers.

00:49:17.321 --> 00:49:18.989 align:middle line:90%
A teacher is only for reference.

00:49:18.989 --> 00:49:21.692 align:middle line:84%
But it is really the
children themselves

00:49:21.692 --> 00:49:25.262 align:middle line:84%
that ask the
questions and discover

00:49:25.262 --> 00:49:26.697 align:middle line:90%
the answers among themselves.

00:49:26.697 --> 00:49:29.366 align:middle line:84%
Only if they've come to the
point where there are either

00:49:29.366 --> 00:49:32.169 align:middle line:84%
no more questions or they can't
figure out the last answer

00:49:32.169 --> 00:49:34.538 align:middle line:84%
is an adult even brought
into the equation.

00:49:34.538 --> 00:49:35.539 align:middle line:90%
And this is in Russia.

00:49:35.539 --> 00:49:38.876 align:middle line:84%
This is an amazingly lit
up group of individuals.

00:49:38.876 --> 00:49:41.011 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: I think what
you're talking about there

00:49:41.011 --> 00:49:43.480 align:middle line:84%
and I really highly recommend
for every one of your viewers

00:49:43.480 --> 00:49:45.516 align:middle line:84%
to try and find this,
the documentary is just

00:49:45.516 --> 00:49:46.217 align:middle line:90%
called School.

00:49:46.217 --> 00:49:48.752 align:middle line:84%
I don't know where you would
find it, but it's phenomenal.

00:49:48.752 --> 00:49:51.889 align:middle line:10%
It's this Russian school that
has completely broken down

00:49:51.889 --> 00:49:54.558 align:middle line:10%
all the boundaries
of the way we teach.

00:49:54.558 --> 00:49:57.728 align:middle line:84%
And the children write the same
exams as all the other schools,

00:49:57.728 --> 00:49:59.697 align:middle line:84%
and they pass them
with flying colors.

00:49:59.697 --> 00:50:00.698 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Flying colors.

00:50:00.698 --> 00:50:03.367 align:middle line:84%
It might be a 12-year-old is
the genius in the physics class,

00:50:03.367 --> 00:50:04.268 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:50:04.268 --> 00:50:06.470 align:middle line:84%
And they explore it out
over a period of weeks

00:50:06.470 --> 00:50:07.605 align:middle line:90%
til they're done.

00:50:07.605 --> 00:50:10.174 align:middle line:84%
Then they go on to whatever
the next subject is.

00:50:10.174 --> 00:50:12.509 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: I saw in that
documentary, some of the kids

00:50:12.509 --> 00:50:14.912 align:middle line:90%
write three years in one year.

00:50:14.912 --> 00:50:17.648 align:middle line:84%
And they finish high school,
and they're 13 years old.

00:50:17.648 --> 00:50:19.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they're developed
on all levels, including

00:50:19.950 --> 00:50:21.051 align:middle line:90%
artistically.

00:50:21.051 --> 00:50:23.654 align:middle line:84%
They are the ones that provide
the artwork for the schools.

00:50:23.654 --> 00:50:25.089 align:middle line:84%
They build the school,
for that matter.

00:50:25.089 --> 00:50:25.856 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: Yes,
they do the building,

00:50:25.856 --> 00:50:27.491 align:middle line:90%
the fixing, the everything.

00:50:27.491 --> 00:50:29.393 align:middle line:84%
So it's a great
model, I believe,

00:50:29.393 --> 00:50:31.795 align:middle line:84%
for an interim phase,
definitely an interim phase.

00:50:31.795 --> 00:50:33.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But it's
still a school.

00:50:33.230 --> 00:50:34.131 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's still a school.

00:50:34.131 --> 00:50:34.999 align:middle line:90%
It's still a school.

00:50:34.999 --> 00:50:36.133 align:middle line:90%
It's an interim phase.

00:50:36.133 --> 00:50:39.103 align:middle line:84%
And there will be
rudimentary classrooms,

00:50:39.103 --> 00:50:41.572 align:middle line:84%
if you want to call them that,
gathering places, where they

00:50:41.572 --> 00:50:44.642 align:middle line:84%
will gather and exchange
information and knowledge

00:50:44.642 --> 00:50:47.745 align:middle line:84%
and experience and learn
other things, where you

00:50:47.745 --> 00:50:49.380 align:middle line:84%
have to watch
somebody do things.

00:50:49.380 --> 00:50:51.815 align:middle line:84%
So yes, of course, there'll
still be classrooms,

00:50:51.815 --> 00:50:53.884 align:middle line:84%
if you want to call them
that, but not the way

00:50:53.884 --> 00:50:56.220 align:middle line:84%
we think of them
today with a board

00:50:56.220 --> 00:50:57.721 align:middle line:84%
and a teacher
there with a stick.

00:50:57.721 --> 00:50:59.924 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't do something
right, you get whacked.

00:50:59.924 --> 00:51:02.293 align:middle line:84%
And we used to get caned
when I was at school.

00:51:02.293 --> 00:51:04.561 align:middle line:84%
Six of the best and
all that kind of stuff.

00:51:04.561 --> 00:51:06.163 align:middle line:84%
If you can't regurgitate
it correctly,

00:51:06.163 --> 00:51:07.031 align:middle line:90%
you're going to fail.

00:51:07.031 --> 00:51:08.232 align:middle line:90%
You're useless to society.

00:51:08.232 --> 00:51:12.336 align:middle line:84%
See, those are the lies and
the levels of hierarchy.

00:51:12.336 --> 00:51:15.873 align:middle line:84%
If you can't regurgitate that,
you're useless to society.

00:51:15.873 --> 00:51:19.677 align:middle line:84%
What kind of education
system is that?

00:51:19.677 --> 00:51:23.180 align:middle line:84%
It is completely perverting
the natural order

00:51:23.180 --> 00:51:26.016 align:middle line:84%
of things, where people
use their God-given talents

00:51:26.016 --> 00:51:27.918 align:middle line:84%
for the benefit of
those around them.

00:51:27.918 --> 00:51:28.485 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, in
the system you're

00:51:28.485 --> 00:51:30.587 align:middle line:84%
talking about, by the
time the child has gone

00:51:30.587 --> 00:51:33.691 align:middle line:84%
through a lot of these basics,
their own innate talents

00:51:33.691 --> 00:51:36.360 align:middle line:84%
and skills are
beginning to surface.

00:51:36.360 --> 00:51:39.296 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: By the time
a child is 12 years old,

00:51:39.296 --> 00:51:42.032 align:middle line:84%
they will know exactly what they
want to do for their community.

00:51:42.032 --> 00:51:43.334 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Can you imagine that?

00:51:43.334 --> 00:51:45.069 align:middle line:84%
I can't even tell you
how many of my adult

00:51:45.069 --> 00:51:46.737 align:middle line:84%
friends still don't
know what they

00:51:46.737 --> 00:51:48.672 align:middle line:84%
want to do with their
lives because they never

00:51:48.672 --> 00:51:51.175 align:middle line:90%
had the luxury of looking at it.

00:51:51.175 --> 00:51:51.875 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Yes.

00:51:51.875 --> 00:51:53.510 align:middle line:84%
So let's just
quickly recap that.

00:51:53.510 --> 00:51:55.612 align:middle line:84%
So the children go through
these mini internships,

00:51:55.612 --> 00:51:56.981 align:middle line:90%
these little workshops.

00:51:56.981 --> 00:52:00.017 align:middle line:84%
And they get longer and longer
the older the children get.

00:52:00.017 --> 00:52:01.385 align:middle line:90%
And they get excited.

00:52:01.385 --> 00:52:03.053 align:middle line:90%
These things are exciting.

00:52:03.053 --> 00:52:05.155 align:middle line:84%
And they stay exciting
because you're not

00:52:05.155 --> 00:52:06.190 align:middle line:90%
cramming it into them.

00:52:06.190 --> 00:52:08.959 align:middle line:84%
You're not forcing them to
do it for extended periods,

00:52:08.959 --> 00:52:11.528 align:middle line:84%
for one year learning
maths and physics that you

00:52:11.528 --> 00:52:13.297 align:middle line:84%
go, why am I
learning this stuff?

00:52:13.297 --> 00:52:13.831 align:middle line:90%
For what?

00:52:13.831 --> 00:52:14.765 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Algebra.

00:52:14.765 --> 00:52:15.632 align:middle line:90%
>>TELLINGER: Exactly.

00:52:15.632 --> 00:52:17.134 align:middle line:90%
Algebra.

00:52:17.134 --> 00:52:19.303 align:middle line:84%
You're going to do it, and
you're going to apply it.

00:52:19.303 --> 00:52:21.505 align:middle line:84%
So when somebody says, well,
actually that's algebra,

00:52:21.505 --> 00:52:23.407 align:middle line:84%
and it works like this,
now you understand.

00:52:23.407 --> 00:52:27.544 align:middle line:84%
How do lenses in cameras work
that can focus in and out?

00:52:27.544 --> 00:52:29.346 align:middle line:90%
You'll find that fascinating.

00:52:29.346 --> 00:52:31.281 align:middle line:84%
Some people will want
to stay with that

00:52:31.281 --> 00:52:35.052 align:middle line:84%
and explore that and turn
it into a whole new science,

00:52:35.052 --> 00:52:39.223 align:middle line:84%
while others will want to go on
developing new types of cheese.

00:52:39.223 --> 00:52:39.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:52:39.990 --> 00:52:41.992 align:middle line:90%
In fact, I had that experience.

00:52:41.992 --> 00:52:45.229 align:middle line:84%
I was awful at math in
school, and partially

00:52:45.229 --> 00:52:47.164 align:middle line:84%
because I couldn't see
the reason behind it.

00:52:47.164 --> 00:52:48.866 align:middle line:84%
If no one could
explain why I needed

00:52:48.866 --> 00:52:52.236 align:middle line:84%
to do this, besides to
balance a checkbook,

00:52:52.236 --> 00:52:55.005 align:middle line:84%
back to the same problem, then
I wasn't really particularly

00:52:55.005 --> 00:52:57.608 align:middle line:84%
motivated, and not a very
good student as a result.

00:52:57.608 --> 00:52:59.877 align:middle line:84%
It was really far
later, when my son, who

00:52:59.877 --> 00:53:02.279 align:middle line:84%
went through the Waldorf
School, which is in that

00:53:02.279 --> 00:53:05.783 align:middle line:84%
school very oriented toward
planting your own seeds

00:53:05.783 --> 00:53:08.685 align:middle line:84%
and harvesting them in the
fall and making your own bread

00:53:08.685 --> 00:53:11.555 align:middle line:84%
and sheering sheep,
and it was really

00:53:11.555 --> 00:53:13.357 align:middle line:90%
a pastoral existence for him.

00:53:13.357 --> 00:53:15.259 align:middle line:84%
But he was taught the
wherefore and the why

00:53:15.259 --> 00:53:17.227 align:middle line:90%
behind the various maths.

00:53:17.227 --> 00:53:19.196 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm embarrassed
to say this, honey,

00:53:19.196 --> 00:53:20.898 align:middle line:84%
but maybe you could
teach me a little bit

00:53:20.898 --> 00:53:23.133 align:middle line:90%
of trigonometry and such.

00:53:23.133 --> 00:53:24.935 align:middle line:84%
Of course, you can
learn it in an instant

00:53:24.935 --> 00:53:27.071 align:middle line:84%
once you understand
the point behind it.

00:53:27.071 --> 00:53:29.339 align:middle line:90%
And that's the thing.

00:53:29.339 --> 00:53:30.741 align:middle line:90%
We are not taught in that way.

00:53:30.741 --> 00:53:32.676 align:middle line:84%
There's no wholeness
to our education.

00:53:32.676 --> 00:53:34.711 align:middle line:84%
So as you say, the
natural brilliance

00:53:34.711 --> 00:53:36.447 align:middle line:84%
can rise right out
of an individual

00:53:36.447 --> 00:53:39.283 align:middle line:84%
at a very early
age in this system.

00:53:39.283 --> 00:53:42.186 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: I see
this as so beautifully,

00:53:42.186 --> 00:53:46.657 align:middle line:84%
naturally progresses from one
area to the next to the next

00:53:46.657 --> 00:53:48.025 align:middle line:90%
until--

00:53:48.025 --> 00:53:50.294 align:middle line:84%
You can imagine by
the time you're 16,

00:53:50.294 --> 00:53:53.964 align:middle line:84%
and in my model at the age of
16 you finish this process.

00:53:53.964 --> 00:53:55.566 align:middle line:84%
At which point, you
would have probably

00:53:55.566 --> 00:54:00.671 align:middle line:84%
undergone a few three to six
month internships between 14

00:54:00.671 --> 00:54:02.773 align:middle line:84%
and 16 because by then
you pretty much know

00:54:02.773 --> 00:54:08.479 align:middle line:84%
what your real passions
and areas of focus are.

00:54:08.479 --> 00:54:10.781 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, you're moving
into a serious internship,

00:54:10.781 --> 00:54:11.482 align:middle line:90%
an apprenticeship.

00:54:11.482 --> 00:54:12.850 align:middle line:84%
>>TELLINGER: Yes,
apprenticeship.

00:54:12.850 --> 00:54:13.517 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:54:13.517 --> 00:54:15.886 align:middle line:84%
And by the time
you're 16, you can

00:54:15.886 --> 00:54:18.689 align:middle line:84%
imagine you've done everything
you can imagine, everything.

00:54:18.689 --> 00:54:20.057 align:middle line:90%
You'll know how to milk a cow.

00:54:20.057 --> 00:54:22.292 align:middle line:84%
You'll know how to build a
rocket, how to put together

00:54:22.292 --> 00:54:25.329 align:middle line:84%
silicon chips to store
memory in a computer.

00:54:25.329 --> 00:54:28.365 align:middle line:90%
You'll know everything.

00:54:28.365 --> 00:54:32.503 align:middle line:84%
There's nobody in the world
that has that kind of foundation

00:54:32.503 --> 00:54:35.072 align:middle line:84%
of knowledge or
information or skills.

00:54:35.072 --> 00:54:38.242 align:middle line:84%
It's completely
alien to us today.

00:54:38.242 --> 00:54:40.110 align:middle line:84%
Most of us don't know
how electricity works,

00:54:40.110 --> 00:54:42.412 align:middle line:84%
why it comes through there
and how it lights up lights.

00:54:42.412 --> 00:54:43.413 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's magic.

